      "span_text": "Because the neutral endopeptidase inhibitor is an epithelial enzyme that plays a major role in the metabolism of tachykinins, such as substance P and neurokinin A (21, 22), Hamamoto et al. suggested that intraesophageal infusion of HCl results in a neural reflex that results in airway release of tachykinins."
